params.text:
Often entrepreneurs skip brand development because they are short on cash and they want to get their product to market as soon as possible.

A solid product strategy is, however, the foundation of a successful startup launch. The Minimum Viable product approach does not require entrepreneurs to spend a lot of time on product development (3 hours in total) and it's proven to result in building compelling market-ready brand, that is based on strategic intent and market insights.

It will help you ensure your internal team is aligned around the same goals, you have a strategy in place that differentiates your product from competitors, and wins the hearts of your early-adopter customers.

The workshop is designed primarily for entrepreneurs and their product and/or marketing teams. It's advised that it is led by an experienced facilitator and that the brand designer is present at the workshop to get a live design brief and be able to ask follow-up questions.

params.text:
1.  Make a list of competitors in the same space and add missing ones

2.  Each person votes on the 2 most important companies on their list

3.  Discuss top voted and choose 2 most relevant comparison/differentiation criteria (y & y axis)

4.  Quickly discuss with the group where on the matrix they should go

5.  Add your brand to the matrix

6.  Double-check: Does this placement make sense for your Why, Values, Audience, and Brand personality?
